3. Outlier Handling

vehicle counts before and after IQR capping

In[5]:
# Store original data for comparison
df['Vehicles_Original'] = df['Vehicles'].copy()

# IQR Method for Outlier Detection and Capping
Q1 = df['Vehicles'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['Vehicles'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

print(f"\n=== Outlier Detection Statistics ===")
print(f"Q1 (25th percentile): {Q1}")
print(f"Q3 (75th percentile): {Q3}")
print(f"IQR: {IQR}")
print(f"Lower Bound: {lower_bound}")
print(f"Upper Bound: {upper_bound}")

# Count outliers
outliers_before = ((df['Vehicles'] < lower_bound) | (df['Vehicles'] > upper_bound)).sum()
print(f"\nNumber of outliers detected: {outliers_before} ({outliers_before/len(df)*100:.2f}%)")

# Apply capping
df['Vehicles'] = np.where(df['Vehicles'] > upper_bound, upper_bound, df['Vehicles'])
df['Vehicles'] = np.where(df['Vehicles'] < lower_bound, lower_bound, df['Vehicles'])

print(f"\nOutliers capped to range: [{lower_bound:.2f}, {upper_bound:.2f}]")

# Visualization
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))

# Before capping
axes[0].boxplot(df['Vehicles_Original'], vert=True)
axes[0].set_title('Vehicle Counts - Before IQR Capping', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Number of Vehicles', fontsize=12)
axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# After capping
axes[1].boxplot(df['Vehicles'], vert=True)
axes[1].set_title('Vehicle Counts - After IQR Capping', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Number of Vehicles', fontsize=12)
axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Drop the temporary column
df = df.drop('Vehicles_Original', axis=1)

LSTM Sequence Preparation

In[14]:
# Prepare sequences for LSTM (24-hour look-back window)
def create_sequences(data, target, look_back=24):
    X_seq, y_seq = [], []
    for i in range(look_back, len(data)):
        X_seq.append(data[i-look_back:i])
        y_seq.append(target[i])
    return np.array(X_seq), np.array(y_seq)

look_back = 24

# For LSTM, we use the full dataset with DateTime ordering
df_sorted = df.sort_values('DateTime').reset_index(drop=True)
traffic_values = df_sorted['Vehicles'].values.reshape(-1, 1)

# Scale for LSTM
scaler_lstm = StandardScaler()
traffic_scaled = scaler_lstm.fit_transform(traffic_values)

# Create sequences
X_lstm, y_lstm = create_sequences(traffic_scaled, traffic_scaled, look_back)

# Train-test split for LSTM
lstm_split = int(len(X_lstm) * 0.8)
X_train_lstm = X_lstm[:lstm_split]
y_train_lstm = y_lstm[:lstm_split]
X_test_lstm = X_lstm[lstm_split:]
y_test_lstm = y_lstm[lstm_split:]

print("\n=== LSTM Sequence Preparation ===")
print(f"Look-back window: {look_back} hours")
print(f"Total sequences created: {len(X_lstm):,}")
print(f"Training sequences: {len(X_train_lstm):,}")
print(f"Test sequences: {len(X_test_lstm):,}")
print(f"\nSequence shape: {X_lstm.shape}")
print(f"  - Number of sequences: {X_lstm.shape[0]}")
print(f"  - Time steps per sequence: {X_lstm.shape[1]}")
print(f"  - Features per time step: {X_lstm.shape[2]}")

# Display example
print("\n=== Example LSTM Input Sequence ===")
print("First sequence (24 hourly values):")
example_seq = scaler_lstm.inverse_transform(X_lstm[0].reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()
example_target = scaler_lstm.inverse_transform(y_lstm[0].reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()[0]
print(f"Input (24 hours): {example_seq[:10]} ... {example_seq[-3:]}")
print(f"Target (25th hour): {example_target:.1f} vehicles")

7. Model Implementation

7.1 LSTM Model for Traffic Volume Prediction

In[15]:
# Build LSTM model
print("\n=== Building LSTM Model ===")

model_lstm = Sequential([
    LSTM(64, activation='relu', return_sequences=True, input_shape=(look_back, 1)),
    Dropout(0.2),
    LSTM(32, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.2),
    Dense(16, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1)
])

model_lstm.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001), loss='mse', metrics=['mae'])

print("\nLSTM Model Architecture:")
model_lstm.summary()

print("\n=== Training LSTM Model ===")
print("Training in progress...")

history = model_lstm.fit(
    X_train_lstm, y_train_lstm,
    epochs=20,
    batch_size=64,
    validation_split=0.1,
    verbose=1
)

print("\nLSTM training complete!")

        'Macro Recall': f"{rec:.4f}",
        'Macro F1-Score': f"{f1:.4f}"
    })
